== Veggie Ragu ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1} into half
moons. Remove the top and bottom from the @carrot{1} (no need to peel), then
halve lengthways and slice into thin half moons. Quarter the @chestnut mushrooms{1}. Finely chop the @chives{1/2}(finely chopped) (or use scissors if you prefer). Drain and rinse the @green lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. When the oil
is hot, add the onion, carrot and mushrooms. Cook, stirring frequently until the
carrot has softened, ~{6-7%minutes}. Add the @Worcester sauce{2} and cook for
~{1%minute} more before stirring in the @chopped tomatoes{1}. Bring to a simmer,
stir in half the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} and leave to cook until the sauce is
thick and tomatoey, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mix the @milk{189%ml} and @water{100%ml} (amount specified in the
ingredient list) in a #jug{}. Melt the @unsalted butter{30%g} in a small
saucepan over medium heat. Add the @plain flour{24%g} and stir to create a sandy
paste. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then slowly pour in the milk and water. Stir
continuously until the sauce is boiling. Add the remaining @vegetable stock pot{1/2}
and cook until the sauce is thick enough to coat the back of a #spoon{}, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Remove from the heat and stir through the chives.

== Assembly ==

When the ragu is cooked, stir in the lentils. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}
to taste.

Lightly oil the bottom of a #baking dish{} and lay in a few sheets of
@lasagne sheets{3} until they cover the bottom evenly, without overlapping
too much. Top with half of the ragu, then add another layer of pasta (break up
the sheets to fill the gaps if necessary). Next, spread over one-third of the
béchamel sauce. First layer done!

Spoon over the remaining tomato sauce, followed by another third of the béchamel
and a final layer of pasta. Mix the chives through the rest of the béchamel and
then spoon this on top of the pasta. Make sure the final layer of pasta is
covered with béchamel. Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g},
then bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the cheese is bubbling and
golden, ~{25%minutes}.

Once cooked, allow the lasagne to sit for ~{5%minutes} (this will help it keep
its shape when you cut into it). Share between your plates and tuck in!